children.name: Text Description
children.characters:
Modals Focus the users attention exclusively on one task or a piece of information
that sits on top of the pages content.

children.name: Text
children.characters: A modal is a dialog that appears over the main content and moves the user into a focussed state of the screen.

children.name: Text
children.characters: Storybook - Click here to see code examples

children.name: Text
children.characters: The prism modal component comes with the following properties which you can see in the right sidebar when you click on the button component itself. You can see usage guidance for each of the properties in more detail below.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
The modal component has a number of slots that enable you to place content inside. To add content swap instances out using the Modal options in the right panel.
Choose a slot to add to (in this case I turned on “Slot 1”)
Change the instance - Search for a local component, or add an existing component from the DS - in this case I added an alert

children.name: Modals are used as containers for focussed content-management actions that appear on top of the app page with a dark overlay. Actions include: Upload Download, export, share Manage alerts Batch edit Manage content details in situ (without leaving page)
children.characters:
Modals are used as containers for focussed content-management actions that appear on top of the app page with a dark overlay. Actions include:
Upload
Download, export, share
Manage alerts
Batch edit
Manage content details in situ (without leaving page)
